'''Phanes Press''' is a [[New Age]] book publishing [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] of [[Red Wheel Weiser Conari]].
Phanes Press was founded by David Fideler in 1985 to publish [[Neoplatonism|Neoplatonic]] and other [[esoteric]] texts. One of its representative and more significant publications was ''The Pythagorean Sourcebook'' translated by [[Kenneth Sylvan Guthrie]] issued in 1987. The company had published 52 titles by 2004, when it was purchased by [[Red Wheel Weiser Conari|Red Wheel/Weiser]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Jim |last=Milliot |title=Red Wheel/Weiser makes two purchases |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-21824492_ITM |work=Publishers Weekly |date=2004-06-28 }}</ref>
